[{"id":"VR799563","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div>Which of the following correctly indicated the direction, if any, of the electric field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector E sub C\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"vector E sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <msub> <mover accent=\"true\"> <mi>E</mi> <mo>→</mo> </mover> <mtext>C</mtext> </msub> </math></span></span> at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>C</mtext></math></span></span> and provides a valid justification?</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n","rubricRef":"VR799563_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span> is located at the center of a circle, which is represented by the dashed line in the figure. Along the top half of the circle is a thin, semicircular ring made of an insulating material containing a uniformly distributed positive charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mo>+</mo> <mi>Q</mi> </math></span></span>. A point charge of the same total charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></math></span></span> is located at the bottommost point on the circle.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows point C at the center of a circle. There is a thin semicircular insulating material with a charge of positive Q across the top of the circle. There is a sphere with a charge of positive Q located below point C on the bottom of the circle and along its circumference.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR799563.g01.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector E sub C\"><math alttext=\"vector E sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>E</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mtext>C</mtext></msub></math></span></span> is zero and has no direction. The semicircle has equal amounts of charge in the left half and the right half.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector E sub C\"><math alttext=\"vector E sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>E</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mtext>C</mtext></msub></math></span></span> is zero and has no direction. There are equal amounts of charge above and below Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span>, all at the same distance from Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector E sub C\"><math alttext=\"vector E sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>E</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mtext>C</mtext></msub></math></span></span> is directed toward the top of the figure. The electric field due to the ring is zero at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span>, so only the point charge contributes to the field.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector E sub C\"><math alttext=\"vector E sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>E</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mtext>C</mtext></msub></math></span></span> is nonzero and directed toward the top of the figure. The electric field at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span> due to the ring is nonzero but less than that due to the point charge.</p>"],"answer":3}]